.TH "IsSpurInBand" 9 "IsSpurInBand" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
IsSpurInBand \- Checks to see if a spur will be present within the IF's bandwidth. (fIFOut +/- fIFBW, -fIFOut +/- fIFBW)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" IsSpurInBand
.BI "(struct MT2063_AvoidSpursData_t *pAS_Info "  ","
.BI "u32 *fm "  ","
.BI "u32 * fp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pAS_Info" 12
Avoid Spurs information block
.IP "fm" 12
If spur, amount f_IF1 has to move negative
.IP "fp" 12
If spur, amount f_IF1 has to move positive

Returns 1 if an LO spur would be present, otherwise 0.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

ma   mb                                     mc   md
<--+-+-+-------------------+-------------------+-+-+-->
|   ^                   0                   ^   |
^   b=-fIFOut+fIFBW/2      -b=+fIFOut-fIFBW/2   ^
a=-fIFOut-fIFBW/2              -a=+fIFOut+fIFBW/2

Note that some equations are doubled to prevent round-off
problems when calculating fIFBW/2
